Edition:
Quote:  A bare-faced attempt was made to enrol the Maoris, who ... were considered to be householders ... within the meaning of the Act. To secure their votes the `flour and sugar' policy was resorted to. It was known that the names of many persons of the right colour - or stamp as it was then called - but ineligible would be forwarded for enrolment, ...
